# u-forge.ai Project Structure Guide

Local-first TTRPG worldbuilding tool with AI-powered knowledge graphs. Built in Rust.

**Status:** Working prototype. CLI demo. Multi-crate Cargo workspace under `crates/`.

## Architecture Overview

Read [ARCHITECTURE.md](mdc:ARCHITECTURE.md) for full details (module map, SQLite schema, resolved bugs, design decisions).

## Workspace Layout

The project is a Cargo workspace. All crates live under `crates/`:

| Crate | Kind | Status | Purpose |
|-------|------|--------|---------|
| `u-forge-core` | lib | Complete | All current source (storage, AI, hardware, queue, search, schema, ingest) |
| `u-forge-graph-view` | lib | Skeleton | Graph view model + layout (see `feature_UI.md`) |
| `u-forge-ui-traits` | lib | Skeleton | Framework-agnostic rendering contracts (see `feature_UI.md`) |
| `u-forge-ui-gpui` | bin | Skeleton | GPUI native app (see `feature_UI.md`) |
| `u-forge-ui-egui` | bin | Skeleton | egui fallback app (see `feature_UI.md`) |
| `u-forge-ts-runtime` | lib | Skeleton | Embedded deno_core TypeScript sandbox (see `feature_TS-Agent-Sandbox.md`) |

`defaults/` (schemas + sample data) lives at the **workspace root**, not inside any crate. `cli_demo.rs` resolves it via `env!("CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR") + "/../../defaults/"`.

## Current Architecture (u-forge-core)

- **Facade**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/lib.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/lib.rs) — `KnowledgeGraph` struct (owns storage + schemas). New bulk methods: `get_all_edges()`, `get_nodes_paginated(offset, limit)`.
- **Storage**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/graph/storage.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/graph/storage.rs) — SQLite via `rusqlite` (bundled). Tables: `nodes`, `edges`, `chunks`, `schemas` + FTS5 virtual table `chunks_fts` + sqlite-vec virtual table `chunks_vec` (768-dim cosine ANN). Key constants: `EMBEDDING_DIMENSIONS = 768`, `MAX_CHUNK_TOKENS = 350`, `DEFAULT_EMBEDDING_CONTEXT_TOKENS = 2048`. `KnowledgeGraphStorage` is the only storage struct.
- **Embeddings**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/ai/embeddings.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/ai/embeddings.rs) — `EmbeddingProvider` trait + `LemonadeProvider` (HTTP) + `EmbeddingManager`.
- **Transcription**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/ai/transcription.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/ai/transcription.rs) — `TranscriptionProvider` trait + `LemonadeTranscriptionProvider` + `TranscriptionManager` + `mime_for_filename()`.
- **Hardware Abstraction**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/hardware/mod.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/hardware/mod.rs) — `DeviceCapability` enum, `HardwareBackend` enum, `DeviceWorker` trait. Sub-modules:
  - [crates/u-forge-core/src/hardware/npu.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/hardware/npu.rs) — `NpuDevice` (embedding + STT + LLM on AMD NPU via FLM)
  - [crates/u-forge-core/src/hardware/gpu.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/hardware/gpu.rs) — `GpuDevice` (STT + LLM on AMD GPU via ROCm; optional embedding via llamacpp; shares `GpuResourceManager` only for STT/LLM, not embeddings)
  - [crates/u-forge-core/src/hardware/cpu.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/hardware/cpu.rs) — `CpuDevice` (TTS via Kokoro; optional embedding via llamacpp)
- **Device Configuration**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/config.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/config.rs) — `DeviceConfig` + `EmbeddingDeviceConfig`. TOML file loading from standard paths; controls device enable/disable state and dispatch weights. Defaults: NPU=100, GPU=50, CPU=10.
- **Inference Queue**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/queue/](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/queue) — `InferenceQueue` + `InferenceQueueBuilder` + `QueueStats`. Five capability channels: `WeightedEmbedDispatcher` (for embeddings), `transcribe_queue`, `synthesize_queue`, `generate_queue`, `rerank_queue`. Per-job retry: up to 3 attempts with exponential backoff in `run_embed_worker`. Weighted dispatch selects highest-weight idle embedding worker, falls back to highest-weight when all busy.
- **Extended Lemonade Integration**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/lemonade/](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/lemonade) — `LemonadeModelRegistry`, `GpuResourceManager`, `LemonadeTtsProvider`, `LemonadeSttProvider`, `LemonadeChatProvider`, `LemonadeStack`, `LemonadeRerankProvider`, `SystemInfo`.
- **Hybrid Search**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/search/](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/search) — `search_hybrid(graph, queue, query, config)` free async function. RRF merge of FTS5 + ANN, optional rerank, graceful degradation.
- **Schemas**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/schema/](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/schema)
- **Data Import**: [crates/u-forge-core/src/ingest/data.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/ingest/data.rs) — JSONL two-pass import.

## Lemonade Integration

**Standard on [Lemonade Server](https://github.com/lemonade-sdk/lemonade)** (AMD, OpenAI-compatible API) for all AI:
- Embeddings: `POST /api/v1/embeddings` (implemented — `LemonadeProvider` in `ai/embeddings.rs`)
- Transcription: `POST /api/v1/audio/transcriptions` (implemented — `LemonadeTranscriptionProvider` in `ai/transcription.rs` for NPU/simple use; `LemonadeSttProvider` in `lemonade.rs` for GPU-managed use)
- Reranking: `POST /api/v1/reranking` (**implemented** — `LemonadeRerankProvider` in `lemonade.rs`; wired into `InferenceQueue` via `rerank_queue`)
- Chat/LLM: `POST /api/v1/chat/completions` (**fully queued** — `LemonadeChatProvider` in `lemonade.rs`; dispatched via `generate_queue` for both GPU llamacpp and NPU FLM models)
- System info: `GET /system-info` (**implemented** — `SystemInfo::fetch()` in `lemonade.rs`; derives `LemonadeCapabilities` from installed recipe backends)

**Linux hardware capability mapping** (derived from `/system-info`):

| Hardware | Recipes/Backends | Capabilities |
|---|---|---|
| AMD NPU (XDNA2) | FLM | `Embedding`, `Transcription` (NpuStt), `TextGeneration` (NpuLlm) |
| AMD iGPU (ROCm/Vulkan) | llamacpp:rocm, llamacpp:vulkan, whispercpp:vulkan | `Transcription` (GpuStt), `TextGeneration` (GpuLlm), `Reranking` |
| CPU | kokoro | `TextToSpeech` |

## Key Integration Points

The `EmbeddingProvider` trait in [crates/u-forge-core/src/ai/embeddings.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/ai/embeddings.rs) is the primary abstraction for embedding work. Only `LemonadeProvider` currently implements it. Do NOT bypass the trait.

The `TranscriptionProvider` trait in [crates/u-forge-core/src/ai/transcription.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/ai/transcription.rs) is the primary abstraction for STT work. Do NOT bypass the trait.

The `DeviceWorker` trait in [crates/u-forge-core/src/hardware/mod.rs](mdc:crates/u-forge-core/src/hardware/mod.rs) is the abstraction for physical compute devices. New hardware backends must implement it.

For new code that needs embedding, transcription, TTS, LLM generation, or reranking: use `InferenceQueueBuilder` to wire up devices and obtain an `InferenceQueue`. Do not call provider HTTP clients directly from business logic.

`LemonadeChatProvider.gpu` is `Option<Arc<GpuResourceManager>>`. Always pass `Some(gpu)` for GPU-backed llamacpp models so they respect the GPU serialisation lock. Pass `None` (or use `new_npu()` / `from_registry_npu()`) for NPU FLM models — they run on dedicated silicon with no shared resource.

`KnowledgeGraph` does **not** hold an `EmbeddingManager` or `InferenceQueue`. Storage and schema operations are fully synchronous and require no running server. All AI capabilities are opt-in — construct them separately when needed.

## Integration Test Threading

Integration tests hit a shared live Lemonade Server. When `LEMONADE_URL` is set,
all modules' integration tests run concurrently by default, causing intermittent
GPU/NPU resource contention on the server side.

**Always run the full test suite with `--test-threads=1` when `LEMONADE_URL` is set.**
`dev.sh` sets this flag automatically when it detects `LEMONADE_URL` in the environment.

```bash
# Correct — single-threaded to avoid server contention
LEMONADE_URL=http://localhost:13305/api/v1 cargo test -- --test-threads=1

# dev.sh handles this automatically
export LEMONADE_URL=http://localhost:13305/api/v1
./dev.sh --backend-only
```

